      "card": {
        "oneLiner": "29F | CC: RLQ abdominal pain x2d | Vitals: HR 98, Temp 37.9, Pain 7/10 | ESI 3 — Crohn's flare pattern, 3rd ED visit for abd pain in 8 months",
        "sections": [
          {
            "id": "approach",
            "title": "Things That Change My Approach",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "S/p laparoscopic ileocecal resection + appendectomy (8/2024) — no appendix present; RLQ pain differential is anastomotic stricture/recurrence or SBO, NOT appendicitis",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "cond-jc-hx-resection",
                    "label": "Medical history - Ileocecal resection/appendectomy 8/2024"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "dr-jc-ct-1114",
                    "label": "CT A/P 11/14/2025"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Combination immunosuppression (adalimumab + azathioprine + prednisone taper) can blunt fever/WBC response — reassuring vitals do NOT exclude abscess/perforation; low threshold for imaging",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "cond-jc-immunosupp",
                    "label": "Problem list - Immunosuppressed state"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "docref-jc-ednote-1114",
                    "label": "ED Discharge Note 11/14/2025"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "med-jc-prednisone",
                    "label": "Active med - Prednisone taper"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Uncertain LMP ('maybe 6 weeks ago'), irregular cycles, not on contraception — pregnancy test pending, must exclude ectopic before proceeding with imaging plan",
                "severity": "act",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "appt-jasmine-cole",
                    "label": "Triage note 7/18/26"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "docref-jc-ginote-0616",
                    "label": "GI Progress Note 6/16/2026"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Colonoscopy 12/18/2025 showed anastomotic recurrence (Rutgeerts i2b) with mild luminal narrowing at the exact site of current pain — raises concern for evolving stricture/partial SBO vs. simple flare",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "dr-jc-colo-1218",
                    "label": "Colonoscopy 12/18/2025"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "bin-jc-pdf-colonoscopy-fax",
                    "label": "Outside colonoscopy report fax 01/06/2026"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Missed 2 adalimumab doses (Apr-May 2026); drug level/antibody testing was pending as of 6/16/2026 — possible subtherapeutic biologic exposure contributing to flare severity",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "docref-jc-ginote-0616",
                    "label": "GI Progress Note 6/16/2026"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "meds",
            "title": "Meds That Matter Now",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Adalimumab (q2wk SC) + azathioprine (daily) — combination immunosuppression increases risk of occult intra-abdominal infection/abscess",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "med-jc-adalimumab",
                    "label": "Active med - Adalimumab"
                  },
                  {
                    "ref": "med-jc-azathioprine",
                    "label": "Active med - Azathioprine"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Prednisone 20mg daily (week 3 of taper) — masks peritoneal signs and fever, complicating exam-based severity assessment",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "med-jc-prednisone",
                    "label": "Active med - Prednisone taper"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Azathioprine — risk of marrow suppression; interpret today's CBC against recent baseline (WBC 9.4 on 6/16)",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "lab-jc-wbc-0616",
                    "label": "WBC 6/16 (azathioprine monitoring)"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Documented morphine intolerance (nausea/vomiting) — use alternative opioid if analgesia needed",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "allergy-jc-morphine",
                    "label": "Allergy - Morphine intolerance"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": "Frequent NSAID use counseled against (flare trigger) — avoid NSAIDs for analgesia today",
                "severity": "caution",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "ref": "soc-jc-nsaid",
